            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "Introduction: Mass spectrometry imaging (MSI) experiments result in complex multi-dimensional datasets, which require specialist data analysis tools. Objectives: We have developed massPixâ€”an R package for analysing and interpreting data from MSI of lipids in tissue. Methods: massPix produces single ion images, performs multivariate statistics and provides putative lipid annotations based on accurate mass matching against generated lipid libraries. Results: Classification of tissue regions with high spectral similarly can be carried out by principal components analysis (PCA) or k-means clustering. Conclusion: massPix is an open-source tool for the analysis and statistical interpretation of MSI data, and is particularly useful for lipidomics applications.",
